The parser shall tokenize aears files
The parser shall generate AST from tokens
When syntax error detected the parser shall report error location
IF malformed syntax THEN the parser shall provide recovery suggestions

The language server shall provide syntax validation
The language server shall offer auto-completion
When hover requested the language server shall display entity information
WHERE LSP client connected the language server shall send diagnostics
WHILE editing active the validation shall run continuously

The extension shall register aears file association
The extension shall provide syntax highlighting
When command invoked the extension shall generate UML diagram
IF file not aears format THEN the extension shall show warning

The generator shall extract actors from entities
The generator shall extract use cases from functionalities
When AST parsed the generator shall create PlantUML output
WHERE relationships detected the generator shall map use case connections

The cli shall accept aears file input
When validation requested the cli shall check syntax
When generation requested the cli shall output UML
IF file invalid THEN the cli shall exit with error code

WHILE parsing active the error handler shall collect issues
When error occurs the system shall preserve partial results
IF critical error THEN the system shall halt processing
The error reporter shall provide line numbers

The file reader shall load aears content
When file changed the watcher shall trigger reprocessing
The output writer shall save generated diagrams
WHERE multiple files the processor shall handle batch operations

